propriate uses of mindfulness that distance People of the Global Majority. A growing emergent movement focused on a justice-infused mindfulness and liberatory wellbeing decolonises mindfulness and de-centres whiteness. Its premise in indigenous, global South, queer knowledges leverages difference to produce multiple solutions focused on liberation. There is room for White Mindfulness to change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMindfulness (Psychology). 0aRacism. 0aSocial service. 0aWhite peoplexRace identity. 7aBODY, MIND & SPIRIT / Mindfulness & Meditation.2bisacsh  aBLM.  aBlack Lives Matter.  aPeople of the Global Majority.  aWhite Mindfulness.  acritical pedagogy.  adecolonisation.  aembodied justice.  amindfulness industry.  amindfulness.  aracism.  asocial justice.  awellness industry.  awellness.  awhiteness.1 aKarelse, Cathy-Mae, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152616207640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526162076423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526162076/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles